Go-Back-N Testing

Test 1 – GBN Data Transfer (0% Loss)

Command

python3 -m go_back_n receiver 5001 5000 4
python3 -m go_back_n sender 5000 5001 4
send hello

Expected

All packets received successfully.
No retransmissions.

Actual

Packets 0–4 acknowledged successfully.
Transfer completed.

Status

PASS

Test 2 – GBN Packet Loss (10%)

Command

python3 -m go_back_n receiver 5001 5000 4 --p 0.1

Expected

Some packets dropped.
Sender retransmits missing packets.
Transfer completes successfully.

Actual

Packet timeouts occurred.
Missing packets retransmitted.
Transfer completed successfully.

Status

PASS

Test 3 – GBN Packet Loss (20%)

Expected:

More retransmissions than 10%.
Transfer still successful.

Actual:

Packet2 timeout
Packet3 timeout
Packet4 timeout
ACKs received after retransmission.

Status:

PASS

Test 4 – GBN Packet Loss (30%)

Expected:

Frequent retransmissions.
Transfer still completes correctly.

Actual:

Several packets retransmitted.
Receiver acknowledged all packets.

Status:

PASS


